-- Beattie Joins Relay Ventures; Brookfield Adds Speers, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-06-28T16:33:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-28/beattie-joins-relay-ventures-brookfield-adds-speers-vlaad-says.html
Standard Chartered Bank appointed
Don Robertson chief executive officer of its Canadian
operations, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Grafton Asset Management formed a structured products team for
oil and gas joint ventures led by Craig Hiddleston, Thomas
Schenk and Scott Hurd, all three joining from Macquarie Energy
Capital and will be based in Calgary.  *  Brookfield Asset Management Inc. (BAM/A)  hired Tara Speers as a senior
associate in private funds from Macquarie Capital Markets Canada
Ltd.  * Desjardins Securities added Mark Lucey as head of research
from Canaccord Genuity, where he was co-head of Canadian
research.  * Relay Ventures appointed Geoff Beattie as chairman. He’s
former CEO of the Woodbridge Co. and former chairman of news and
information provider Thomson Reuters Corp.  * Rob Knowles joined Integral Capital Markets in Calgary as an
energy research analyst from MGI Securities.  * Beacon Securities Ltd. added Lisa Abraham as director of
equity trading from Acuity Investment Management where she was
head of trading.  * The Public Sector Pension Investment Board in Montreal added
Genevieve Maltais-Boisvert as manager of infrastructure
investments. Maltais-Boisvert was most recently with QGC, the
Australian unit of  BG Group Plc. (BG/)   * Greg Kitscha joined Infrastructure Ontario as project manager
in the transit and civil infrastructure group, from Forum Equity
Partners where he was a senior associate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
